<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">26</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">3</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">May 1 2006</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">641</span> - <span property="pageEnd">657</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16702444/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16702444</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2006.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: May 1 2006</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.263055162">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keyword</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=PEG+%3D+polyethylene+glycol&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">PEG = polyethylene glycol</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Because of its capacity to provide accurate information about the severity and extent of Crohn disease, CT enterography is becoming the first-line modality in the evaluation of patients with suspected inflammatory bowel disease.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><d